<plot>Trey and Donny are two rich playboys, living the good life. At a party, Trey, an actor whose claim to fame was on a Spanish-language sitcom, suggests to Donny, an auteur director, that they jet over to Vegas and shoot a movie. As Donny accepts the challenge, the two conceptualize the movie from cast to character to plot, their freeform brainstorm appearing on the screen. They have competing interests - Donny's need to create the next great story versus Trey's desire to simply end up with the girl - but collaborate to create a film that shifts, reshapes, and ultimately becomes complete, a story that Trey and Donny become proud to call their own, Adventures in Vegas.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?024207</url></doc>
